item.title: CVE-2019-19167|2024-08-05T02:09:39.368Z -- tobesoft -- nexacro14
item.description: Tobesoft Nexacro v2019.9.25.1 and earlier version have an arbitrary code execution vulnerability by using method supported by Nexacro14 ActiveX Control. It allows attacker to cause remote code execution.
